<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Exports to Russia Doubled in 1993 </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Exports to Russia Doubled in 1993 </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504123194 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1000 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504123194 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finland's trade with Russia has taken a clear upward 
turn. Exports to Russia doubled last year compared to the 
previous year. According to a review by the Board of Customs, 
the value of the exports was just over 6,000 million Finnish 
markkas [FMk]. Imports increased by 17 percent from 1992 and 
were worth FMk7,800 million. Last year's trade with Russia 
exceeded the trade with the Soviet Union in 1991, but still 
remained considerably smaller than in the final years of the 
eighties. 

</TEXT>

