<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demirel: Albania `Trusted Partner' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demirel: Albania `Trusted Partner' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0504185494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0504185494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] Albanian President Sali Berisha, who is in 
Turkey on an official visit, has participated in a luncheon 
given in his honor by President Suleyman Demirel at the Cankaya 
Mansion. At the luncheon, Demirel said that Bulgarian-Turkish 
relations have reached a level that can serve as an example to 
the region and to the rest of the world. 
  Demirel expressed Turkey's concern regarding the tragic and 
inhuman situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina spreading to Kosovo, 
Sandzak, and Vojvodina and indicated that he has been constantly 
warning concerned countries and international organization about 
this issue. 
  [Begin Demirel recording] Turkey is making efforts to 
establish democracy, peace, and stability in the Balkans. We 
vehemently oppose coerced border changes and genocide with an 
aim to form ethnically pure countries. We view Albania, which 
shares our views and has a significant place in the region, as a 
true friend and a trusted partner in establishing peace and 
stability in the Balkans. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

