<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ankara Says Changes in Cyprus CBM's `Unfair' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ankara Says Changes in Cyprus CBM's `Unfair' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0604090594 Istanbul HURRIYET in Turkish 5 Apr 94 p 14 </F>
<F P=103> NC0604090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul HURRIYET </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara--Turkish officials told Robert Lamb, U.S. 
coordinator for Cyprus Affairs, in Ankara yesterday that the 
Turkish Cypriot side will not make any concessions. 
  Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin held talks with Robert Lamb 
yesterday morning and informed him that the changes made in the 
confidence-building measures [CBM's] are unfair. He also 
informed Lamb that it is impossible to agree to the changed CBM 
package. 
  Meanwhile, Ambassador Tugay Ulucevik, deputy under secretary 
of the Turkish Foreign Ministry who is also responsible for 
Cypriot affairs, said that the Turkish Cypriot side must not be 
expected to make additional sacrifices. He said that the Greek 
Cypriot side is the one that should be approached. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

