GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0504182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] The Central Bank has fixed the official effective 
selling rate of the U.S. dollar for tomorrow at 32,149 Turkish 
lira [TL] and the German mark at TL18,978. According to these 
rates, the U.S. dollar rose 38.8 percent and the German mark 39 
percent against today's prices. The official effective buying 
rate of the U.S. dollar for tomorrow has been fixed at TL31,956 
and the German mark at TL18,864. 

