  [Text] Silvio Berlusconi has decided to call off 
negotiations with the Northern League. The meeting scheduled to 
take place tomorrow has been postponed. 
  "From today, the leader of Forza Italia said during the 
course of a news conference, we will go neither to the Northern 
League nor to any other side. We will await the decision of 
President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro who is scheduled to appoint the 
next prime minister, and we will be at his disposal in order to 
form a new government." 

