<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fini Responds to Bossi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fini Responds to Bossi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0504165894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1617 GMT 
5 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0504165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] "The Northern League has not fully understood the 
elementary distinction between government and institutional 
reform: It must be clear that the government does not in any way 
have the task of reforming the institutions." 
  Gianfranco Fini, the leader of the National Alliance, was 
replying to Umberto Bossi. Fini added that "presidentialism is 
the only corner in government where federalism can exist, but 
federalism does not mean overturning the article of the 
Constitution which assigns primary functions to the State and 
residual functions to the regions". Fini then recalled that 
there could not be a parliamentary majority without either the 
Northern League or the National Alliance. 

</TEXT>

