<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Albanian President on Turkey's Efforts in Balkans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Albanian President on Turkey's Efforts in Balkans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0504172894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1545 GMT 5 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0504172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 5 (A.A.) -- Albanian President Sali 
Berisha, who is currently in Turkey, said on Tuesday [5 April] 
that Albania gave priority to friendly ties with Turkey. 
  Berisha spoke at a luncheon in his honor. 
  "Turkey and Albania have strong traditional, historical, and 
cultural relations," Berisha said. "Albanian people will always 
respect Turkish people and Gazi Mustafa Kemal Ataturk, the 
founder of modern Turkish Republic." 
  "He (Ataturk) founded the contemporary Turkish Republic with 
his political and military genius, extraordinary courage, and 
determination." 
  He also said Turkey is a strong, peaceful, and stable 
element 
in its region and played an important role in preserving peace, 
security, freedom and democracy within the framework of North 
Atlantic Treaty Organization. 
  The guest president spoke on Turkey's efforts in the Balkans 
and said that Turkey can have a vital role in the crisis in 
Bosnia. 
  "The concern that the war in Bosnia could spread to southern 
parts of the Balkans affected the improvement of the reforms 
that were put into practice in Albania," he said. 
  Berisha said its impossible to provide stability in the 
Balkans without finding the true solution for Kosovo problem. 
  He said his country welcomed the presence of Turkish 
soldiers 
in Bosnia. 
  "Turkish soldiers are going to Bosnia for peace and will 
spend efforts to contribute to peace," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

