<H3> <TI>   Aviation Agreement Signed With Belarus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aviation Agreement Signed With Belarus </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3103151994 Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG in German 31 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU3103151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIENER ZEITUNG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Aviation Agreement"] </F>
  [Text] An aviation agreement between Austria and Belarus 
was concluded at the Foreign Ministry in Vienna on 29 March 
1994. On the part of Belarus, the agreement was signed by 
Transportation Minister Stepan Shkapich, an on the Austrian side 
by Ambassador Wolfgang Wolte, head of the Economic Department in 
the Foreign Ministry. 
  Under the agreement, which is the legal basis for a regular 
airline service between the two countries, both sides grant each 
other rights for certain routes. Air traffic between Vienna and 
Minsk has been started both by Austrian Airlines and the 
Belarussian air carrier Belevia. 

</TEXT>

