<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   More on League's Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    More on League's Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604155694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1629 GMT 
6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A two-stage government: The first cabinet would be a 
constituent one and would last a few months. The prime minister 
-- not necessarily from the [Northern] League -- would have to 
be a "staunch federalist." He would chair a governmental 
committee which would submit to parliament a bill for a new 
constitution. The second period would be political. The 
government would last five years altogether. This is the 
League's latest proposal to overcome the impasse. It was made 
by Roberto Maroni. 
  Before that, the speakers of both chambers must be elected. 
The League has asked to meet Forza Italia, the National 
Alliance, the Christian Democratic Center, and the Lista 
Pannella on Monday [11 April]. 

</TEXT>

