<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Anti-European Union Party To Be Formed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Anti-European Union Party To Be Formed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704115694 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1000 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704115694 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A new party will be set up in the political center. 
The New National Center [Uusi Kansallinen Keskusta], UKK, 
intends to contest the next Diet elections with full candidate 
lists in all election districts. UKK calls for the 
implementation of a policy independent of European Union 
legislation and the pursuit of an independent foreign and 
security policy based on neutrality and the Finnish desire to 
defend the country. 
  The chairman of the temporary board which is preparing for 
the registration of the party is Ilkka Hakalehto from Helsinki. 
Pentti Kettunen, a former Diet deputy of the SMP [Finnish Rural 
Party] from Kajaani, is deputy chairman. Both men also belong 
to the leadership of the Finnish People's Independence Front, 
which opposes membership in the European Union. 

</TEXT>

