<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on Temporary Power Aid to Iraq </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry on Temporary Power Aid to Iraq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0704073594 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2120 
GMT 6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0704073594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] It has been announced that Turkey has been 
extending electrical power aid to northern Iraq since 3 April. 
Speaking at his weekly news conference, Foreign Ministry 
spokesman Ferhat Ataman said that Turkey has been supplying the 
region with 20 megawatts of power by using the lines between 
Silopi and Zakho. He recalled that the Iraqi Administration has 
not been able to supply the Province of Dahuk with power since 
last August. We have taken this step to temporarily solve the 
problem confronting the Iraqi people, he said. 
  Ataman stressed that this aid should be assessed within the 
framework of the humanitarian aid Turkey extends to Iraq. It is 
important, he said, for the Iraqi Government to recreate the 
conditions whereby it can supply power to the region. 
  According to information supplied by the Foreign Ministry 
spokesman, the Turkish Red Crescent extended a total of 7,098 
tonnes of food to 1,007,955 persons in Dahuk, Irbil, and 
Sulaymaniyah during the past six months. 

</TEXT>

