  [Text] The Central Bank has fixed the official effective 
selling rate of the U.S. dollar for tomorrow at 40,052 Turkish 
lira [TL] and the German mark at TL23,361. According to these 
rates, the U.S. dollar rose 24.5 percent and the German mark 23 
percent against today's prices. The official effective buying 
rate for the U.S. dollar for tomorrow is fixed at TL39,813 and 
the German mark at TL23,221. 
  Meanwhile, yesterday's activity in the free foreign exchange 
markets is continuing today. The U.S. dollar, which was 
TL30,400 when the free market closed yesterday, opened up to 
transactions at TL33,000. The U.S. dollar which continued to 
rise during the day reached TL39,500 in certain exchange 
bureaus. The German mark started the day at TL21,000 and closed 
at TL22,500. 

