<H3> <TI>   Environmental Agreement Signed With Poland </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Environmental Agreement Signed With Poland </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704093494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0827 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Schwerin (DDP/ADN) -- Germany and Poland signed an 
agreement on cooperation in the area of environmental protection 
in Schwerin today. Federal Environment Minister Klaus Toepfer 
and his Polish counterpart Stanislaw Zelichowski signed the 
agreement after a meeting of the German-Polish environmental 
council. The agreement includes stipulations on the exchange of 
environmental data. The parties to the agreement commit 
themselves to taking all appropriate and effective measures to 
prevent, reduce, and combat any considerable cross-border 
environmental damage. 
  The environmental council of the two countries determines 
the 
guidelines and strategies for cross-border cooperation. An 
initial environmental agreement was signed with Poland in autumn 
1989. 

</TEXT>

