<F P=106> ["Exclusive" interview with SPD Chairman Rudolf Scharping by </F>
Miriam Mrizova; place and date not given: "Rudolf Scharping 
Claims in Exclusive Interview for SME: German Government 
Spokesman Is Deceiving"] 
  [Excerpt] [Mrizova] Accusations have appeared in the 
German news to the effect that Chancellor Kohl has bribed 
correspondents in the Federal Press Office who create an image 
of you as an incompetent politician. The Social Democrats 
supposedly want to address a complaint to the Federal 
Constitutional Court in this matter. 
  [Scharping] With its propagandistic contributions, the 
Federal Press Office is increasingly abetting the present 
government, its spokesman Dieter Vogel is deceiving parliament, 
and his office is infringing upon political neutrality that is 
prescribed by the Constitution. Because State Secretary Vogel 
is responsible for the Federal Press Office, he should bear the 
consequences for this affair and resign from his post. The 
Social Democratic Party of Germany [SPD] will use all 
parliamentary means to resolve this situation. It is now 
working on a motion that will initiate a ban on the continued 
publication of such contributions by the Federal Press Office. 
