<H3> <TI>   CDU/CSU Plans Higher Excise, Property Taxes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CDU/CSU Plans Higher Excise, Property Taxes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0504134994 Hamburg DER SPIEGEL in German 4 Mar 94 p 16 </F>
<F P=103> AU0504134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DER SPIEGEL </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Higher Taxes?"] </F>
  [Text] The leaders of the Christian Democratic Union 
[CDU]/Christian Social Union [CSU] Bundestag group are 
considering higher excise and property taxes and the 
introduction of a road-use charge. Gasoline tax is not to be 
raised any further. This is envisaged by a still secret concept 
that CDU/CSU Bundestag Group Chairman Wolfgang Schaeuble intends 
to present this summer. In the medium term, payroll and income 
tax are to be reduced, investments are to be promoted, and a 
capital formation plan could open up additional leeway in wage 
policy for working people and trade unions. Schaeuble has 
declared the concept "top secret" (according to a CDU deputy). 
Finance Minister Theo Waigel (CSU) has not yet been informed. 
He is afraid of a discussion about tax increases before the 
Bavarian Landtag elections in September. 

</TEXT>

