<H3> <TI>   Kohl Views German-British Responsibility for Europe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Views German-British Responsibility for Europe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704093694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0919 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0704093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
stressed that Great Britain and Germany have a "great 
responsibility" for the development of a Europe that is oriented 
toward a market economy and is socially fair. This is 
particularly true at the present time, which is "characterized 
by far-reaching political changes throughout Europe," Kohl 
underlined in a welcoming address, published in Bonn today, to 
the participants of the 44th Koenigswinter conference in 
Cambridge. He is sure that this German-English political 
discussion will provide fresh and "forward-looking stimuli" in 
both countries. 

</TEXT>

