<H3> <TI>   `Dozens of Kurds' Deported to Turkey in Past Year </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Dozens of Kurds' Deported to Turkey in Past Year </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604141194 Hamburg DPA in German 1242 GMT 6 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0604141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hamburg (DPA) -- Last year and this year dozens 
of Kurds have been deported from Germany to Turkey without this 
becoming known to the general public. According to a DPA 
inquiry on Wednesday [6 April], in January and February 1994 31 
Kurds were forcibly sent back to their homeland from Lower 
Saxony; 24 were deported on the basis of the asylum law and 
seven on the basis of the aliens' law. The other laender said 
regarding this problem that deportations are listed not 
according to ethnic groups but according to citizenship. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

