<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bundesbank Cuts Third Key Rate Again </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bundesbank Cuts Third Key Rate Again </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0604104594 Hamburg DPA in German 0912 GMT 6 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0604104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Frankfurt/Main (DPA) -- The Bundesbank has again 
loosened its interest reins very slightly: In the latest 
security transaction under repurchase agreement, it allotted 
short-term money to the banks at the marginal interest rate of 
5.73 percent -- 0.03 percentage points under the previous level; 
80.4 billion German marks [DM] were allotted, relevant 
transactions for DM82.1 billion had become due. 
  The great majority of the allotments ranged from 5.73 to 
5.75 
percent. The rate for security transactions under repurchase 
agreement is regarded as the central bank's third key rate. 
Because of the volume, it is far more important for the money 
market than the classic discount and Lombard key rates, which 
are currently 5.25 and 6.75 percent respectively. 

</TEXT>

