<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Switzerland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Official Resigns Over `Blue Helmet' Dispute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Party Official Resigns Over `Blue Helmet' Dispute </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0704152394 Bern ATSA/SDAA Database in French 1351 GMT 6 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0704152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern ATSA/SDAA Database </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ATSA/SDAA report: "Swiss Blue Helmets; Martin Chevallez </F>
Leaves ASIN Vice Presidency"] 
  [Text] Lausanne, 6 Apr (ATS) -- Colonel Martin Chevallez 
has left the vice presidency of Action for an Independent and 
Neutral Switzerland (ASIN), whose president is National Council 
member Christoph Blocher (UDC [Swiss People's Party]/ZH). He 
confirmed the report published on Wednesday [6 April] by the 
dailies 24 HEURES and TRIBUNE DE GENEVE. 
  He had headed the ASIN campaign in French-speaking 
Switzerland against the European Economic Area (EEA) during the 
federal vote on 6 December 1992. But he now supports, against 
his president, the creation of a Swiss UN Blue Helmet corps, on 
which a federal vote will be taken on 12 June. Martin 
Chevallez, son of former Federal Council Member Georges-Andre 
Chevallez, was EMG [expansion unknown] lieutenant colonel and a 
professional training officer until 1992. After being granted 
leave by the Federal Military Department to devote himself to 
his anti-EEA campaign, he became a militia colonel and commander 
of the Fifth Mountain Infantry Regiment in 1993. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

