<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Fereydun Bakhtiari Authorized To </F>
Enter Switzerland"] 
  [Text] Bern, 7 Apr (ATS) -- Fereydun Ilkhan Bakhtiar [name 
as received] has been granted approval to enter Switzerland. He 
thus will be able to register as an asylum seeker, Federal 
Refugee Office (ODR) spokesman Heinz Schoeni said Thursday [7 
April]. A cousin of the former shah's prime minister, Shapur 
Bakhtiar, arrived at Geneva Airport without a passport on 22 
March. Claiming to be in danger if he was sent back to Tehran, 
he spent the intervening period in Cointrin's [Geneva airport] 
transit area, under threat of expulsion back to Iran. 

</TEXT>

