<H3> <TI>   Bavaria To Deport 20 Kurds to Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bavaria To Deport 20 Kurds to Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    8 Deportation Orders Issued </H4>

<F P=102> AU0804100594 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 0900 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0804100594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bavarian Interior Minister Beckstein announced in 
Bonn today that the Free State will continue to deport violent 
Kurdish criminals. Expulsion orders will also be issued. After 
the riots and the Augsburg superhighway blockade, Bavaria 
expects to issue a total of 20 deportation orders, eight of 
which have already been issued, he said. The interior minister 
stressed that, in his opinion, there is no general obstacle to 
deportation to Turkey. Therefore, he intends to enforce such 
measures. 

</TEXT>

