<H3> <TI>   Eurofighter Costs To Increase </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Eurofighter Costs To Increase </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804141694 Berlin DIE WELT in German 8 Apr 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0804141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DIE WELT </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["rmc/DW"-signed report: "Eurofighter Will Cost DM300 </F>
Million More Than Planned"] 
  [Text] Bonn -- The development of the Eurofighter 2000 
aircraft will probably cost more than originally planned. 
Germany's share in the development costs alone will at least be 
300 million German marks [DM] more than planned. An expert in 
the Federal Audit Court even expects the costs to increase by 
DM700 million. The reason is that, on the instructions of 
Defense Minister Volker Ruehe of the Christian Democratic Union, 
the industry must make the controversial Eurofighter less 
powerful and thus cheaper. In view of Ruehe's request to force 
the unit price of the European fighter aircraft below DM100 
million, the additional costs have become inevitable, the German 
general contractor, German Aerospace (Dasa) has stated. The 
DM300 million are made up of DM145 million caused by the longer 
duration of the project, DM100 million in inflation 
compensation, and a remainder resulting from a change in the 
guidelines for the calculation of profits. All in all, Dasa has 
requested DM570 million from the German defense budget for the 
development of the Eurofighter 2000. A government decision on 
the procurement of the fighter aircraft has been announced for 
1995. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

