<H3> <TI>   First No-Confidence Vote Against Balladur Proposed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    First No-Confidence Vote Against Balladur Proposed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704150694 Paris France-2 Teletext in French 1355 GMT 7 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704150694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, the Socialist and Communist Party groups in 
the National Assembly, as well as some members of the Republique 
et Liberte group, proposed the first no-confidence motion 
against the Balladur government. 
  Drawn up on the initiative of the Socialist Party, the 
motion 
criticizes the Balladur government's record since it came to 
power a year ago and calls for the repeal of the five-year law 
on employment. 
  The 83 MPs who signed the motion say that the law "relies on 
the deregulation of labor, the massive insecurity of 
employment...and the undermining of the status of employees." 

</TEXT>

