<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Observers in Hebron To Have `Political Function' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Observers in Hebron To Have `Political Function' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0604123994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1100 GMT 
6 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0604123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri stressed that "the 
functions of the Italian observers in Hebron will essentially be 
political, and to provide security for the local population." 
  "The fact that all the sides asked for our soldiers to take 
part in the operation along side troops from Denmark and 
Norway," Fabbri added, "shows how much prestige Italy has 
acquired during these peacekeeping operations." 
  Referring to Somalia, the minister said, "It was the most 
demanding operation that our troops have taken part in since the 
Second World War, because of the loss of life that we endured." 

</TEXT>

