<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Says EU Decision `Wrong Move' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Says EU Decision `Wrong Move' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0704190794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1700 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0704190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis referred to the 
European Commission decision to refer Greece to the European 
Court over its measures against Skopje [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] in the following way: 
  [Begin Arsenis recording] This wrong move encourages 
destabilization in the region. It encourages the powers that be 
not to move toward settling the issue through dialogue and 
initiatives but to maintain their unreasonable positions. It is 
a move that ultimately praises the intransigent. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

