<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin Expresses Support for Denktas on CBM's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Expresses Support for Denktas on CBM's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0704152494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1455 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0704152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 7 (A.A.) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin on Thursday [7 April] expressed support for Turkish 
Republic of Northern Cyprus (TRNC) President Rauf Denktas. 
Cetin said that Denktas' attitude toward the UN 
confidence-building measures [CBM's] is justified and positive. 
Cetin said that the TRNC is rightly reacting to additional 
elements of the confidence-building measures and that this is 
from whence the problem stems. 
  The confidence-building measures involve the opening of the 
Lefkose [Nicosia] Airport to international traffic and the 
inhabited Maras [Varosha] section to UN monitoring. 
  UN-sponsored intercommunal talks on Cyprus were interrupted 
last July. 
  Cyprus has been divided since 1974 when Turkey conducted a 
peace operation to the island following a Greek-backed coup 
which attempted to annex the island to Greece and to annihilate 
its Turkish Cypriot population. 
  The TRNC came to existence in 1983. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

