<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mentese Returns From Security Talks in Romania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mentese Returns From Security Talks in Romania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0804072894 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0804072894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has concluded his 
official visit to Romania and has returned to Turkey. In a 
statement at Esenboga Airport, Mentese said that in his talks in 
Romania, positive developments were achieved on the issues of 
domestic security and drugs and arms smuggling. He added that 
the Turkish delegation is continuing the talks. Pointing out 
that Turkey has candid relations with Romania on the issue of 
terror, Mentese said that Romania has detained certain PKK 
[Workers Party of Kurdistan] members. He noted that terror will 
be defeated in Romania as well. In reply to a question, Mentese 
said Greece should stop supporting the PKK, recalling that it is 
the duty of all world countries to fight terrorism. 

</TEXT>

