<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bonn Suspends Weapons Deliveries to Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn Suspends Weapons Deliveries to Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804113494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1041 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0804113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The German Government has 
confirmed the suspension of all weapons deliveries to Turkey. 
Government Spokesman Dieter Vogel said today that Bonn was 
obliged to investigate whether material from German deliveries 
to Turkey was being used in Turkey's conflict with the Kurds. 
  Vogel said the government is in possession of reports to 
this 
effect from Germans who were recently in Turkey. He admitted, 
however, that it would be difficult to prove whether the 
suspected items from stocks of the former GDR National People's 
Army in fact originated from German supplies, and not from sales 
by former Warsaw Pact states. 
  The government spokesman at the same time confirmed that 
Bonn 
favors, in principle, the deportation of militant Kurds from 
Germany. It must, however, be guaranteed that the expellees are 
threatened neither with the death sentence nor with torture in 
Turkey. If a relevant agreement is signed with Turkey, the 
German Government has "not the slightest doubt" Ankara would 
adhere to it. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-18716 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu068_i_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
