<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Death of Rwandan, Burundian Presidents Deplored </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Death of Rwandan, Burundian Presidents Deplored </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0704140194 Paris Radio France International in French 1230 
GMT 7 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0704140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] French Minister for Cooperation Michel Roussin 
said he was dismayed at the news of the death of the Rwandan and 
Burundi presidents. Here is a statement by the spokesman of the 
French Foreign Ministry Richard Duque: 
  [Begin Duque recording] First, France deplores the brutal 
death of the Rwandan and Burundian presidents. We would like to 
extend our condolences to the families of the presidents and to 
the families of the other victims. You also know that the crew 
were French. We deplore their deaths and extend our condolences 
to their families as well. We do not have any particular 
information on the circumstances in which the plane of the 
Rwandan president crashed yesterday evening. We think that 
there is a need for an international investigation in order to 
find out precisely what caused the crash and who was 
responsible. [end recording] 
  An emergency meeting was held this morning in Paris. There 
were representatives of the presidency, the prime minister, and 
of the ministries of defense and foreign affairs. The French 
forces based in Bangui, in the Central African Republic, have 
been put on alert. [passage omitted] According to the 
government, there are 600 French nationals in Rwanda and 700 in 
Burundi. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

