<H3> <TI>   Government Plans Evacuations From Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Plans Evacuations From Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Two Planes Depart </H4>

<F P=102> BR0804120594 Brussels RTL-TVI Television Network in French 
1100 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BR0804120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels RTL-TVI Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by RTL-TVI newscaster David Oxley] </F>
  [Text] A Sabena 737 Boeing is to leave Brussels airport in 
the hour for Bujumbura. The plane will be used as a shuttle 
between Bujumbura and Kigali so as to proceed with the 
evacuation of the Belgian nationals. A maximum of 150 people 
will be allowed on each flight. A Sabena DC-10 will also leave 
as soon as possible for Entebbe. 

</TEXT>

