<F P=100> BENELUX COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Plans Evacuations From Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Plans Evacuations From Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Paracommandos Ready </H4>

<F P=102> LD0804111294 Brussels Radio 1 Network in Dutch 1000 GMT 8 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio 1 Network </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Our country is keeping two batallions of 
paracommandos standing by for a possible evacuation of our 
fellow countrymen in Rwanda in Africa. The BELGA news agency 
learned this from government circles. Some 800 paracommandos 
were put on standby as early as yesterday evening. They are 
standing by to evacuate the 1,500 Belgians in Rwanda and if 
necessary, also other foreigners, should the Belgian Government 
so decide. The Cabinet reconvenes at 1500 hours [1400 GMT] to 
discuss the situation in Rwanda. It will decide whether an 
evacuation will be launched. 
  At the military airport of Melsbroek, security has been put 
on standby. However, the men have received the direct command 
to say nothing. 
  France, too, is said to be considering deploying its troops 
in the central African republic for a possible evacuation of its 
fellow countrymen, but for the time being, no decision has been 
made. There are some 600 French in Rwanda, most of them living 
in Kigali. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

