  [Text] Belgium and France have decided to clarify the 
situation. Brussels and Paris are saying that it is out of the 
question to do anything other than protect foreign nationals. 
Listen to this reaction to events in Rwanda from Blaise 
Compaore, the president of Burkina Faso. He is currently in 
France: 
  [Begin Compaore recording] We felt a lot of pain when we 
heard the news because we believe that the Rwandan people do not 
deserve this. However, we can see that Africa, unfortunately, 
is going to go through many other tests before it achieves its 
democratization, because we have historic limits which prevent 
us from going forward at the rate hoped for by the people and 
even by the international community, but we trust that the 
Africans will manage to establish their nations and, of course, 
to preserve their freedoms. This, of course, will have to be 
with the support of the international community. [end recording] 

