<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assistance Requested To Evacuate Nationals From Kigali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assistance Requested To Evacuate Nationals From Kigali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0904180394 Paris AFP in English 1713 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0904180394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Vienna, April 9 (AFP) -- Austria has asked 
France, Belgium and Germany to evacuate if necessary 15 
Austrians living in the strife-torn Rwandan capital, Kigali, the 
Foreign Ministry said Saturday [9 April]. 
  The Austrian civilians would be flown out of the country, 
where savage ethnic fighting has left at least 1,000 dead in the 
last three days, along with citizens of the three other 
countries, under the protection of French and Belgian troops. 
  Austria also has some 40 nationals serving with United 
Nations peacekeeping troops deployed in Rwanda as part of a 
transition scheme ahead of elections planned for next year. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

