<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greens Recommend No Vote </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greens Recommend No Vote </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104102594 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 11 Apr 94 pp 1, 6 </F>
<F P=103> AU1104102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "kett": "Greens' No to European Union Is Now </F>
Set"] 
  [Excerpt] Vienna -- Austrian People's Party [OeVP] 
Chairman Erhard Busek indicated on Saturday [9 April] that his 
party will not make a recommendation for the European Union [EU] 
referendum on 12 June. In contrast, Karl Krammer, chief of 
Chancellor Franz Vranitzky's cabinet, stated that a party has to 
take a clear position on such an important question. 
  Yesterday, Sunday, the Greens set their "no." The party is 
to make a relevant "recommendation without patronizing" for the 
referendum at the end of April. Yesterday, the extended federal 
executive committee agreed unanimously on this. Federal 
Spokesman Peter Pilz stated that he had submitted the relevant 
motion to the committee. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

