<H3> <TI>   Curtails Romania Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Curtails Romania Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804151894 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in 
English 1300 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The foreign ministers of Belgium and Romania have 
signed a joint political declaration. The two foreign ministers 
have tackled the prospects of the Partnership for Peace program, 
bilateral cooperation, and Romania's ties with the European 
Union. The Belgian minister, Mr. Claes, underlined the necessity 
for Romania to extend its initiatives for closer cooperation 
with the European Union. 
  Mr. Claes has decided to cut short his visit in Romania and 
return to Belgium to examine the situation in Rwanda where 
Belgian blue helmets have been killed. Romanian Foreign 
Minister Teodor Melescanu has said that among the Belgian blue 
helmets deployed under UN aegis in Rwanda there is also a group 
of Romanian observers who are safe. 

</TEXT>

