<H3> <TI>   Government Issues Communique </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Issues Communique </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804174694 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels La Une Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We now have the main points of the communique issued 
by the restricted cabinet meeting convened this afternoon. 
  First, there is an appeal to UN Secretary General Butrus 
Ghali. On behalf of the government, the prime minister and the 
foreign minister reminded the UN secretary general of the urgent 
need to reinforce the safety of the Blue Helmets stationed in 
Rwanda. Mr. Butrus Ghali made remarks to that effect today. 
  The government also expressed its concern for the safety of 
Belgian nationals living in Rwanda. This terse sentence 
follows: The government stresses that it has consequently 
decided on measures needed to guarantee the safety of our 
nationals. No further details are given. These measures can be 
interpreted as the protection of Belgians living in Rwanda and, 
most probably, an operation to evacuate them. 

