<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Parties Comment on NATO Strikes in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials, Parties Comment on NATO Strikes in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kinkel: `Justified, Necessary' </H4>

<F P=102> LD1104091094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0743 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104091094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cologne (DDP/ADN) -- Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel 
described the NATO air strike against the Serb advance on the 
east Bosnian town of Gorazde as "justified, necessary, and also 
right." On Westdeutscher Rundfunk's morning magazine program 
today, Kinkel expressed "hope that the Serbs will now come to 
their senses; otherwise NATO may be forced to intervene there 
again." This is possible according to UN Security Council 
resolution 836. "We are dealing here with one of the UN's safe 
areas which may be protected if force is used [against it] 
without any further decisions [being necessary]," the foreign 
minister stressed. 
  At the same time Kinkel spoke in favor of making further 
progress in the political field. It is of prime importance that 
the Russian side plays a part, he said. Kinkel called on Russia 
to exert its influence on the Serbs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

