<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Parties Comment on NATO Strikes in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials, Parties Comment on NATO Strikes in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    SPD: `Correct Step' </H4>

<F P=102> LD1104093394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0746 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Saarbruecken (DDP/ADN) -- Hans-Ulrich Klose, the 
leader of the SPD [Social Democratic Party] group in the 
Bundestag, has said the NATO operation at Gorazde was a correct 
step. Speaking on Saarland Radio today, Klose said: "The 
United Nations resolutions are constantly being violated; now 
the United Nations has reacted." 
  In certain situations the international community has no 
other option but to reply to force with force. 
  Klose said he was skeptical about a unanimous stance by the 
UN Security Council toward the Serb troops. To him, Russia's 
real role in the conflict remained unclear. On the other hand, 
the determination of the Americans regarding the Serbs had 
obviously grown. 

</TEXT>

