<H3> <TI>   Government Organizes Rwanda Evacuations Via Bujumbura </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Organizes Rwanda Evacuations Via Bujumbura </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1004081594 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0705 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1004081594 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Early today, the German Government 
set in motion the evacuation of German nationals affected by the 
civil war in Rwanda. The Press Office of the Foreign Ministry 
stated that, on instructions from Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel, 
Harald Ganns, the German Government's commissioner for African 
policy, has been flown by Bundeswehr aircraft to Bujumbura to 
organize the return of Germans arriving there from Rwanda. 
  The Defense Ministry has provided a 200-seater aircraft. The 
Foreign Ministry reported that approximately 180 Germans -- 
chiefly development aid workers and their families -- are in 
Bujumbura. They reached safety in Burundi yesterday from 
war-torn Rwanda. 
  It was stated that Kinkel has issued instructions that other 
foreign nationals who had to flee Burundi would be flown out on 
the Bundeswehr aircraft if there are any free spaces. 

</TEXT>

