<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Envoy Meets Official on Arms Export Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkish Envoy Meets Official on Arms Export Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0804155094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1523 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0804155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, April 8 (A.A.) -- Turkey's ambassador to 
Germany Onur Oymen had a talk today with German Federal Foreign 
Ministry State Secretary Dieter Kastrup, on the suspension of 
German arms supply to Turkey. 
  After the meeting, Oymen told the Anatolian Agency, "we 
asked 
from Germany to resolve the matter at the soonest, through 
diplomatic means." 
  During their talk the German side told Oymen that they have 
received reports on Turkey's violation of the Turkish-German 
agreement and that Turkey was using German arms it received 
within the NATO, for domestic security reasons. 
  They added that Germany has suspended arms supply to Turkey 
until their investigation on the matter is concluded. 
  Oymen told German officials that Turkey has not violated any 
agreement it signed so far and that these claims were fabricated 
by circles supporting the illegal terror organization. 
  "Friendly and allied countries should trust each other," 
Oymen said. 
  "The claims have no basis. We expect Germany to resolve the 
matter at the soonest, through diplomatic channels," he said. 

</TEXT>

