<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Right-Wing Party Office Destroyed in Arson Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Right-Wing Party Office Destroyed in Arson Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904115294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1048 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0904115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cologne (DDP/ADN) -- The party office of the 
right-wing extremist German League in Cologne was completely 
destroyed Friday night [8 April] in an arson attack. All files 
and documents were also destroyed in the fire, which took 
several hours to put out. Markus Beisicht, party chairman and 
Cologne city council representative, estimated that material 
damage amounts to well over 50,000 German marks. 
  By midday, no letter admitting responsibility had been 
received. However, it is assumed that the perpetrators came from 
left-wing anarchists, because of several calls in Cologne by an 
"Antifascist Alliance" for the "destruction of the temporary 
offices." In Beisicht's view, the attack means the work of the 
party will be completely paralyzed for the next few weeks. The 
German League, nonetheless, will take part in the Cologne local 
government elections as planned. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

