<H3> <TI>   Military Planes To Aid Evacuation From Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Planes To Aid Evacuation From Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1004145294 Paris AFP in English 1448 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1004145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rome, April 10 (AFP) -- Three Italian aircraft due 
to help in the evacuation of foreign nationals from Rwanda took 
off from Pisa airport Sunday afternoon [10 April] en route for 
Nairobi. 
  The three Hercules C-130 transport planes of the Italian 
armed forces left the military base in the central Italian town 
at around 3:00 p.m (1300 GMT), the Italian defence ministry said. 
  The planes, carrying 24 paratroopers, will participate in 
the 
evacuation of European and U.S. citizens from the Rwandan 
capital Kigali as soon as conditions at the city's airport 
permit, the ministry said. 
  The ministry earlier said it was in permanent contact with 
the Belgian and French general staffs, which it said had set up 
a centre in Nairobi to coordinate the evacuation of westerners 
from Rwanda. 
  More than 1,000 people have been killed in the east African 
state in a wave of ethnic bloodletting which began Thursday. 

</TEXT>

