<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister on Costs of Joining EU </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister on Costs of Joining EU </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0904140094 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1300 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0904140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to Interior Minister Mauri Pekkarinen, 
Finland's EU [European Union] negotiation result is getting 
worse and worse while the contents are becoming more exact. 
According to Pekkarinen, who spoke in Marttila, the result is 
clearly worse than expected both in regional policy and in the 
food industry. According to Pekkarinen, membership of the EU 
would create extra costs of nearly 10 billion Finnish markkas 
for next year's state budget. According to him, what is now 
fundamental is which national measures are to be taken. 
According to the minister of the interior, the national 
referendum should be arranged only after the Swedish national 
referendum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

