<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Visits U.S. Bases in Crete </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Visits U.S. Bases in Crete </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1004184794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1700 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1004184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis today visited the 
installations of the U.S. military base in Gournes, Crete. The 
bases will be turned over to the Greek Government tomorrow after 
30 years of U.S. Administration. 
  Arsenis said the bases will not be used for military 
purposes 
and added that the committee that has been established for this 
purpose will examine ways of utilizing the bases' buildings and 
territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

