<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Bomb Attacks; 17 November Claims Responsibility </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Bomb Attacks; 17 November Claims Responsibility </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104052894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0400 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1104052894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An anonymous caller has telephoned a private radio 
station claiming that 17 November was responsible for explosions 
that took place shortly after midnight at the offices of the 
Alico and Nationale Nederlanden insurance companies. 
  The explosion at Alico's office on 119 Kifisias Avenue was 
caused by a 3.5-inch rocket launched from a construction site 
across the road. The explosion at Nationale Nederlanden's 
office on 131 Kifisias Avenue was caused by a timed explosive 
mechanism. The caller who made the claim on behalf of the 17 
November organization also said that a few days ago, a British 
aircraft carrier was selected as a target by the organization 
but the launching mechanism failed. 
  Around the same time as the explosions in Kifisias Avenue, a 
blast occurred by a parked car at 3 Kanaris Street, Stamata, 
Attiki. The investigating authorities believe this explosion is 
not related with the two bomb attacks on Kifisias Avenue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

