<H3> <TI>   Demonstration Leaders Captured </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Demonstration Leaders Captured </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104132894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Security forces have captured 26 persons after 
determining that they caused an outbreak during an unauthorized 
demonstration in Ankara yesterday condemning the intense Serbian 
attack in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  According to a statement issued by the Ankara Governor's 
Office, it was determined that these persons provoked the crowd, 
and caused the stoning of the UN representation, the U.S. 
Embassy, the TRT General Directorate building, and the True Path 
Party headquarters. Noting that these persons were captured with 
Molotov cocktails, hammers, and assault knives in their 
possession, the statement adds that an investigation into the 
incident is under way. 
  On the other hand, an inquiry was started in Istanbul into 
the unauthorized demonstration condemning Serbian aggression 
which was held in Taksim. The Prosecutor's Office opened an 
investigation into two private television channels who aired the 
demonstration held in Taksim. Officials of the Bakirkoy and 
Kucukcekmece Chief Public Prosecutor's Office stated that they 
placed a request to TGRT [TURKIYE Radio and Television] and 
Inter Star for the videotapes of the demonstration. The 
officials stated that, if necessary, the concerned parties of 
the two private channels may be taken to court on charges of 
provoking and encouraging the public to commit crimes. 
  The authorities further stated that the slogans and placards 
used during the demonstration in Istanbul's Taksim Square are 
being analyzed and if found offensive necessary legal steps will 
be taken. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

