BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Bosnia-Herzegovina Vice President Ejup Ganic and 
Foreign Affairs Minister Irfan Ljubijankic met with Foreign 
Minister Hikmet Cetin today. In a statement before the meeting, 
Cetin said that Turkey is pleased with the first step taken by 
the Bosnians and Croats toward coexistence, the Washington 
Agreement. 
  [Begin Cetin recording] We hope and wish, like Mr. Ganic 
said, that the other link of this development is completed soon, 
that is, that the Serbs also participate in this multiracial, 
multireligious, and multicultural independent Bosnia-Herzegovina 
federation. Turkey is continuing to conduct relations both with 
the officials of Bosnia-Herzegovina and with the Croats. We are 
also continuing to conduct a dialogue with the Serbs. [end 
recording] 
  Ganic said: Without the participation of Turkish diplomacy, 
it is impossible to achieve peace and stability in the Balkans. 

