<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reports on Visit of Bosnian Vice President </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    B-H Officials Meet Demirel, Ciller </H4>

<F P=102> TA0904071794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0904071794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Suleyman Demirel today received 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Vice President Ejup Ganic and Foreign Affairs 
Minister Irfan Ljubijankic, who are currently visiting Ankara, 
at the Cankaya Mansion and conferred with them for some time. 
Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin also attended the meeting. 
  According to the President's Press Center, during the 
meeting, Ganic briefed Demirel on the agreement reached between 
the Muslims and the Croats as well as the latest situation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. Ganic also invited Demirel to Sarajevo. 
Demirel said that he will undertake such a visit at a suitable 
time. 
  Ganic also met with Prime Minister Tansu Ciller in Ankara. 
In a statement after the meeting, Ganic declared that the 
latest situation in Bosnia-Herzegovina was discussed during his 
talks with Demirel, Ciller, and other Turkish officials. Ganic 
concluded by saying that he conveyed to Ciller the gratitude of 
the Bosnian people for her visit to Sarajevo. 
  The visiting vice president and foreign minister later 
concluded their contacts in Ankara and proceeded to Istanbul. 
In a predeparture statement at Ankara's Esenboga Airport, Ganic 
reported that the talks on the future of his country were very 
beneficial. He expressed the conviction that Turkey's support to 
his country will continue with regard to protecting 
Bosnia-Herzegovina's territorial integrity and finding a 
peaceful solution to the problem. The Bosnian officials were 
seen off at Esenboga Airport by Cetin. 

</TEXT>

