<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-069 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  10 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sees Role for Turkey in Peace Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sees Role for Turkey in Peace Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1104062794 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2000 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1104062794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israel Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres, who arrived 
in Ankara today on an official visit, has started to hold 
contacts. He first visited Motherland Party leader Mesut 
Yilmaz. Replying to journalists' questions during the meeting, 
Peres said that with its modern and secular structure, Turkey is 
exemplary in the Islamic world. Replying to a question, he said 
that Turkey can assume an effective role in the Middle East 
peace process. He added that Turkey can participate in the 
presence to be deployed in Jericho and Gaza. 
  Asked what Israel expects from Turkey, Peres replied: Turkey 
is the only Muslim country that is friends with both the Arabs 
and Israel. Consequently, it can constitute a bridge factor. 
  Shim'on Peres then met with Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin 
for 
30 minutes. Cetin later gave a dinner in honor of the visiting 
foreign minister. 

</TEXT>

