<H3> <TI>   Cetin Replies to Christopher Letter on Cyprus Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Replies to Christopher Letter on Cyprus Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0904181094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0904181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of Cetin, Christopher] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has said that the 
United States should intensify its initiatives concerning the 
Greek Cypriot side if progress is to be achieved in the Cyprus 
talks. Cetin replied to a letter on the Cyprus issue he 
received from U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher. 
According to information obtained by a Turkish Radio and 
Television correspondent, in his reply letter Cetin said that 
one should remain loyal to the original package the UN secretary 
general issued on 1 July, 1993, regarding the 
confidence-building measures. He pointed out that the UN 
secretary general announced that Kliridhis, leader of the Greek 
Cypriot administration, accepted the package in question. 
  In his letter, Christopher said that a significant point has 
been reached on the Cyprus talks, adding that a great 
opportunity has been created. He further thanked Turkey for the 
efforts it exerted on the issue and noted the benefits of 
encouraging the negotiating process. 

</TEXT>

