<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EC Commissioner Criticizes Greece Over FYROM Embargo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EC Commissioner Criticizes Greece Over FYROM Embargo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804174394 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 
1600 GMT 8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon Radio Renascenca </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Portuguese EC Commissioner Joao de Deus Pinheiro 
stated that the trade embargo imposed by Greece on The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM] is illegal and a shot in 
the foot of the present European presidency. In an exclusive 
interview with Renascenca, Deus Pinheiro states categorically 
that the Macedonia issue poisoned things during the Greek 
presidency: 
  [Deus Pinheiro] They have let things be poisoned by the 
Macedonia issue and have created some friction both in relations 
with the member states and in the relations of the presidency 
with other institutions. Thus a decision by the Commission 
yesterday to take the case of The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia to the court of justice. 
  I believe that this decision by the Greek Government to 
impose a trade embargo on The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia--as far as I am concerned--is not only illegal in 
terms of Community law but also, politically, a shot in the foot. 
  [Annuoncer] That was Joao de Deus Pinheiro in an exclusive 
interview with Renascenca which will be broadcast in its 
entirety tomorrow in the Por Ca e Por La program, at 1100 hours. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

