  [Text] And there have, of course, also been initial 
reactions to the NATO air strike from Bonn. The German 
Government is hoping for concessions from the Serbs and a 
continuation of the cease-fire talks in the former Yugoslavia. 
Government spokesman Dieter Vogel said, and I quote: the 
attackers of Gorazde only have themselves to blame for this 
response from NATO, which was carried out on behalf of the 
