<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Visit; Hot Line Established </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Visit; Hot Line Established </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0804141194 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 
8 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0804141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] A red phone, Moncloa-Kremlin, hot line 
linking Madrid and Moscow is to be one of the improvements in 
bilateral ties with Russia that is being prepared 70 hours 
before Boris Yeltsin's first official visit to Spain. Over to 
Maria Jesus Chao at the Council of Ministers in Moncloa Palace. 
  [Chao] The Council of Ministers has agreed to install a 
direct confidential telephone line linking Moncloa Palace to the 
Kremlin, as well as the signing of seven agreements between 
Spain and Russia. The occasion is Boris Yeltsin's official visit 
to our country. 
  These agreements are contained in the friendship and 
cooperation treaty between both countries and are meant to 
strengthen economic, industrial, cultural, educational, and 
environmental cooperation. They will also cover social security 
and labor relations issues. 

</TEXT>

