<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arsenis Hopes For `No More' NATO Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arsenis Hopes For `No More' NATO Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1104092994 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0900 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1104092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Referring to yesterday's attack in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, National Defense Minister Yerasimos Arsenis 
expressed the hope that there will no more attacks by NATO. 
Arsenis described NATO and the United Nations as organizations 
not properly equipped to deal with situations like the crisis in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. He also gave an assurance that he is 
following the situation closely. 

</TEXT>

