<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Comment on Serb Attack, NATO Airstrike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Comment on Serb Attack, NATO Airstrike </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Ciller Condemns Serb `Chemical Attack' </H4>

<F P=102> TA1004150394 Ankara ANATOLIA in Turkish 1420 GMT 10 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1004150394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ankara (AA) -- Prime Minister Tansu Ciller has 
condemned the chemical attack on the Bosnian city of Gorazde by 
the Serbs. She said: "Our government is following the 
developments with utmost care and is conducting the necessary 
contacts." 
  Ciller issued a statement in connection with the 
developments 
in Gorazde. 
  According to the Prime Minister's Press Center, the 
statement 
is as follows: 
  "To my great horror and regret, I have learned that today 
the 
Serbs used chemical weapons against the town of Gorazde in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, which has been subjected to an inhuman siege 
by the Serbs for a long time, and that many civilians, children, 
and elderly people were killed in this attack. 
  ``I strongly condemn this attack, which is difficult to 
believe and constitutes a crime against humanity, on behalf of 
my government and myself. We want the international community, 
particularly the United Nations and NATO, to take the necessary 
steps without any further delay to put an end to the suffering 
of the people of Bosnia-Herzegovina and punish the culprits. 
Our government is following the developments with utmost care 
and is conducting the necessary contacts. 
  ``I pray for those who lost their lives in this attack and I 
wish the wounded a speedy recovery. I extend my deepest 
solidarity to the victims' families.'' [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

